{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δρῦς</b>, ἡ <br /> (Pelop. ὁ, <i>accusative</i> to [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 401, compare “IG” 9(1).485.5 (from Thyrrheum), but _feminine_ in 4th c.AD(?): Arcadius Grammaticus, “Schwyzer” 664.23): _genitive_ δρυός: _accusative_ δρῦν (δρύα 4th c.AD(?): Quintus Smyrnaeus Epicus 3.280): _nominative_ _plural_ δρύες 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.132, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 832, etc., δρῦς 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 2.9.2, 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 8.12.1: _accusative_ _plural_ δρῦς 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 528, “Nu.” 402, δρύας 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 403, 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Delum” 84, “Anthologia Graeca” 7.8 (Antip. Sid.): _genitive_ δρυῶν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.218: dual δρύε Hdn.Gr. 1.420 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]. [ῠ, except in δρῦς, δρῦν: <i>genitive</i> δρῡός at the beginning of a verse, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 436]\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—originally, <b>tree</b> (δρῦν ἐκάλουν οἱ παλαιοὶ.. πᾶν δένδρον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.86, compare 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; including various trees, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 3.8.2 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>Quercus Aegilops</b> (φηγός) and <b>Quercus Ilex</b> (πρῖνος),[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare ἡ φηγὸς καὶ ἡ πρῖνος εἴδη δρυός 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.106 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; opposed to πεύκη, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.494 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to πίτυς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.186, compare 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.389, 23.328, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; στέφανος δρυός crown <b>of oak leaves</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 2588.7 (Delos, 2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; commonly, <b>the oak,</b> δ. ὑψικάρηνοι, ὑψίκομοι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.132, 14.398, compare 13.389, 23.328, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; sacred to Zeus, who gave his oracles from the oaks of Dodona, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.328; αἱ προσήγοροι δρύες 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 832; πολύγλωσσος δ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1168, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 275b: proverbial, οὐ γὰρ ἀπὸ δρυός ἐσσι.. οὐδ᾽ ἀπὸ πέτρης\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] thou art no foundling from <b>the woods</b> or rocks, i. e. thou hast parents and a country, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.163, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 34d, “R.” 544d, “Anthologia Graeca” 10.55 (6th c.AD: Palladas Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but οὐ μέν πως νῦν ἔστιν ἀπὸ δρυὸς οὐδ᾽ ἀπὸ πέτρης.. ὀαρίζειν 'tis no time now to talk at ease from <b>tree</b> or rock, like lovers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.126 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀλλὰ τί ἦ μοι ταῦτα περὶ δρῦν ἢ περὶ πέτρη; why all this about <b>trees</b> and rocks (i. e. things we have nothing to do with)? [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 35 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also διὰ πέτρας καὶ διὰ δρυὸς ὁρᾶν 'to see through a brick wall', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.1083d. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of other trees bearing acorns or mast [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 8.1.6), πίειρα δρῦς\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] the resinous <b>wood</b> (of the pine), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 766 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the olive, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 615 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. θαλασσία, ={ἁλίφλοιος}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pseudo-Democritus Alchemista “Symp.Ant.” p.5G. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> δ. ποντία, <b>gulf-weed, Sargassum vulgare,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 4.6.9. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>worn-out old man,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anthologia Graeca 6.254 (Myrinus Epigrammaticus), 2nd c.AD: Artemidorus Daldianus Onirocriticus 2.25 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]. (Cogn. with δόρ; cf. Sanskrit <i>dru-</i> 'wood', in compounds)","strongNumber":"G6972","accentedUnicode":"δρῦς","shortDef":"an oak","mediumDef":"an oak","stepGloss":"an oak","stepTransliteration":"drus","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}